    <bodyText>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>We will accept up to 100% of child maintenance income. However it cannot be the only form of income on an application.</p>
<p>Any children associated with the maintenance payments should be entered as financial dependents.</p>
<p>To verify income we'll need the latest 3 months’ bank statements showing receipt of payments on all cases.</p>
<p><strong>We'll also need 1 of the following:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><span class="list-bullets">a copy of a Court Order</span></li>
<li><span class="list-bullets">Maintenance Assessment letter from the Child Support Agency</span></li>
<li><span class="list-bullets">a written private agreement drawn up between the separating parties.</span></li>
</ul>
<p>If any payment has been missed in that period, then the income cannot be used as part of the affordability assessment.</p>]]></Value>
